  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0ddd\u0da7\u0dd2 111 \u0d9a\u0dd4\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0db1\u0dba \u0d9a\u0dc5 \u0dc0\u0dd1\u0db1\u0dca \u0dbb\u0dae\u0dba\u0da7 \u0daf\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba\u0ddd\u0d9c\u0dba",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The order given to the van that transported 111 crores of drugs",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Criminal Investigation Department's Illegal Assets Investigation Division says that the car seized by the police for transporting a consignment of drugs worth 111 crore rupees in Weligama area of \u200b\u200bMatara was issued prohibition orders under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act.",
        "On November 20, 2020, according to the information received by the officers of the Police Special Task Force Gonahena camp, the police said that this large-scale drug raid had been conducted with 111 kilos of drugs.",
        "After the raid, 13 people involved in the drug trafficking were arrested in the investigations carried out by the Police Narcotics Bureau.",
        "A person residing in Angoda Kotikawatta who was illegally transporting the drug was arrested and during the long investigation it was revealed that the person had bought this car with the money earned illegally from drug trafficking.",
        "A police officer said that the long investigation revealed that the car was purchased by the drug trafficker at a car dealership in Colombo 6, Kirulapana High Level Road area on July 27, 2020 for a sum of Rs. ."
      ],
